Differential expression analysis along erythroid trajectory¶

Berge et al., 2020 tradeSeq

For tradeSeq we need weights to asign cells to trajectoris. That is not yet possible with RNA-velocities or CellRank. With monocle3 it is very difficult to use the results from Scanorama. The best way forward seems to be slingshot which has a direct interaface to tradeSeq and uses the existing results e.g. cluster, UMAP, etc.

General Tutorial and for perturbation along the trajectory

so <- subset(so, subset=leiden_annotation %in% c("Ery (1)", "Ery (2)", "Ery (3)", "Ery (4)", "Ery (5)", "Ery (6)"))
sce <- as.SingleCellExperiment(so, assay="RNA")
In [10]:
# Run slinshot 
sce <- slingshot(sce, clusterLabels='leiden_annotation', reducedDim='X_UMAP', start.clus="Ery (1)")
write.csv(data.frame(pseudotime=sce$slingPseudotime_1, cell_id=colnames(sce)), "result/slingshot/pseudotime.csv")
